oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Twenty-Sixth Annual Conference (1993). Opening Ceremony, Los Amigos Round-Up Extravaganza, and Tours
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The 26th Annual AABP Convention was launched on Thursday evening, September 16 with true AABP hospitality and friendship. On Saturday evening, September 18, AABP members and spouses boarded buses and headed to Los Amigos, along the Rio Grande River under giant shady Cottonwood trees on the Sandia Indian Reservation. Several tours were available for Convention participants.
